{{fr-pron|m|f=laquelle|mp=lesquels|fp=lesquelles}}

# {{lb|fr|relative|following a preposition}} [[which]], [[that]], [[whom]]
#: {{ux|fr|Elle préfère l'homme avec '''lequel''' tu sortais.|She prefers the man with '''whom''' you were going out.}}
#: {{ux|fr|Il se remet à travailler sur le projet pour '''lequel''' il avait déjà passé tellement de temps.|He's starting to work on the project on '''which''' he had already spent so much time.}}
# {{lb|fr|interrogative}} [[which]] one
#: {{ux|fr|Passe-moi le ballon. ― '''Lequel''' ? Il y en a trois.|Pass me the ball. — '''Which one'''? There are three of them.}}

====Usage notes====
* As a relative pronoun, ''lequel'' can refer to people or things (unlike {{m|fr|qui}}, which can only refer to people after a preposition). After the prepositions {{m|fr|entre}} and {{m|fr|parmi}}, ''lequel'' must be used whether it refers to a person or a thing.
* As an interrogative pronoun, ''lequel'' must agree in gender and number with the noun it replaces. As a relative pronoun it must agree with the antecedent of the relative clause.

====Related terms====
* {{l|fr|n'importe lequel}}
* {{lb|fr|Louisiana}} [[équel]]
